constructor.details: ERC721 construcor takes a 'name' and a 'symbol' to the token collection.

params.baseURI: - set the i_baseTokenURI for the NFT collection
params.name: - set the name of the NFT token collection
params.symbol: - set the symbol of the NFT token collection
params.whitelistContract: - initialize an instance of the Whitelist contract

mint().details: mint allows a user to mint 1 NFT per transaction after presale ended

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

presaleMint().details: presaleMint allows a user to mint one NFT per transaction during presale

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setPaused(bool).details: setPaused makes the contract paused or unpaused

startPresale().details: startPresale starts a presale for the whitelisted addresses

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw().details: withdraw the Ether to the owner of the contract

s_baseTokenURI.details: i_baseTokenURI for computing {tokenURI}. If set, the resulting URI for each token will be the concatenation of the 'baseURI' and the 'tokenId'
